ting tools , environments or courses for  ame  ame language  ame ( abbreviated call ) . ^ +  ame programme : ^ the provisonal programme is available at ^  ebsite ^ the 2-weeks programme comprises the following courses : ^ * introduction to call (  ame :  ame  ame , [  ame of  ame ] ) ^ * introduction to natural language processing for call (  ame :  ame  ame [  ame of  ame ] ) ^ * introduction to speech processing for call (  ame :  ame  ame [  ame  ame ] ) ^ * using  ame tools in call ( hands-on ) (  ame :  ame  ame [  ame of  ame ] ) ^ * using speech tools in call ( hands-on ) (  ame :  ame  ame [  ame of  ame ] ) ^ * call design and interfaces (  ame :  ame  ame [  ame  ame ] ) ^ * grammatical and morphological error diagnosis (  ame :  ame  ame [  ame of  ame ] ) ^ * systems for pronunciation training (  ame :  ame  ame [  ame  ame ] ) ^ * building a grammatical call system ( hands-on ) (  ame :  ame  ame [  ame of  ame ] ) ^ * building a speech call system ( hands-on ) (  ame :  ame  ame [  ame of  ame ] ) ^ all students attend the same full programme , except for the hands-on sessions , where students can sign up for either  ame or speech oriented streams . ^ in special student sessions students can present their own work . ^ the presentations will be published on the  rg website . ^ please note that the number of places for this summer school is limited and that early registration is recommended . ^ the working language of the  ame school will be english . ^ +  ame : ^  ame registration  ame ( euro )  ame  um academic staff  um commercial organisations  um  rg members are entitled to a  um discount ^ +  ame and accommodation : ^ the cost of accommodation ( on campus ) will be  um euro per night meals will be free . ^ +  ame , grants and other information : ^ for detailed information about registration procedures and deadlines , fees , accommodation ,  ame possibilities , venue , course and social programme , etc visit the  ame website at ^  ebsite ^ or send a